name: adenosylhomocysteinase
comment: The enzyme contains one tightly bound NAD+ per subunit. This appears to bring about a transient oxidation at C-3' of the 5'-deoxyadenosine residue, thus labilizing the thioether bond [2] (for mechanism, click here), cf. EC 5.5.1.4, inositol-3-phosphate synthase.

references.title: The enzymatic synthesis of S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine from adenosine and homocysteine.
The mechanism of action of S-adenosylhomocysteinase.
